  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "`kubectl logs -f` doesn't work for Windows node.\r\n\r\nAfter some investigation, I think the problem is that for Docker the log file `kubectl logs` reads is a symlink to the actual docker container log file.\r\n\r\nOn linux, I believe fsnotify follows symlink by default https://github.com/fsnotify/fsnotify/issues/199, so it works on linux.\r\n\r\nHowever, on windows I believe it doesn't follow the symlink. I tried to replace the symlink file with an actual file and append log to it, `kubectl logs -f` will start working after that.\r\n\r\nThe proposed solution is to explicitly follow the symlink in Kubelet, so that we get more consist behavior across different platforms.\r\n",
